      • getCalendars

        public static java.util.List<ServerCalendar> getCalendars(java.lang.String XMLResponse)
                                                   throws javax.xml.parsers.ParserConfigurationException,
                                                          org.xml.sax.SAXException,
                                                          java.io.IOException
        Method getCalendars parses the XML response, which should contain all collections returned by PROPFIND request (see propfind_calendars.txt). Than is selects only the collections, which appear to be a Calendar (have their calendar-order, calendar-name and calendar-color set not to null). These collections are returned as ServerCalendar objects in a single List.
        Parameters:
        XMLResponse - String reponse to a PROPFIND request
        Returns:
        list of ServerCalendars
        Throws:
        javax.xml.parsers.ParserConfigurationException
        org.xml.sax.SAXException
        java.io.IOException
